rComments: Professor Rector is so wonderful! He cares about student success and takes time to meet with you, to see how you're feeling and give helpful feedback. Do your readings as it's important to engage in-class discussion. I had a 3h lecture online with this professor, yet he still made it interesting due to his passion for the subject. Would recommend
Rector is a great prof. Tough grader though, so you will really have to work hard if you want a good grade. He likes when people participate in class.
Great prof

Graded attendance worth 10% (which is actually to your benefit if you show up). Hard to reach during office hours because there's always a line of people. Always glad to answer questions and help with assignments though. Nice guy but HARD marker. I went to the writing centre and showed up to every single class and still only got a B in this class.
Do the readings and participate in class. It's an English course, that's really it.

He was my first year poetry prof and it was by far one of the hardest classes Ive ever taken. A really nice guy, but lectures went past the end of classes and he often would go off topic. A very hard marker when it came to papers, as well.

While he may be a good in class lecturer, though boring at times, Rector is a very hard marker. He loves to listen to himself talk, and talk he will. GO TO OFFICE HOURS, a friend of mine went and got extra credit just for showing up before the second paper was due.

He's a little confusing on what he wants but overall I really liked him. He's very open to other people's interpretation. There was a lot of reading but they were interesting and the lectures themselves were pleasant, probably the class I attended the most this semester.
Lots of homework for an English course, but Rector is such a great lecturer, and the reading is so interesting, you wont mind.

Fully expected to hate Medieval Lit, and because of him it ended up being my favourite class of the semester. Very interesting lectures, and he's so passionate about what he teaches. Ended up having to ask for my grades the day before the exam because I hadn't received any of them yet, but found him to be a very fair marker regardless.

Rector is such a gem! Yes, he is disorganised, but he is so helpful and friendly in office hours, you should definitely talk to him about your paper before writing it. He assigns difficult assignments, but I learned so much in his class. He's hilarious, charismatic, fun, and you can tell he cares about you and the material. He's my favourite prof!
Unclear about what he expects from his assignements.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Quirky and interesting prof but the amount of assignments he expects is extreme. Only received about marks for about 30% of our grade before the final exam and had to hand in 50% (final and a 10 page paper) of your grade within one day. Expectations aren't very clear and grading is inconsistent BUT if you go to his office hours he is helpful.
Might receive your assignments back by graduation

Assignments are unclear and feedback is totally unhelpful. Don't expect to get an exam layout beforehand or to know your mark before entering the exam. Lectures are scattered and attendance is on random days that will supposedly reflect your actual attendance. Charismatic teacher but bad for your gpa.
He's awesome. I'd recommend any class with him.

Based on his quirky humour throughout the lectures, and his complete willingness to help you outside of class, he's a great prof. Then you get an essay back with a completely unexpected horrible mark, and are forced to memorize 20 lines of Middle English (not only tedious, but completely useless & unneccessary) and your judgment completely changes

I was in Medieval Literture with Rector this semester and in total disagreement with the below comment. Expectations were clear, lectures were engaging and marks were very fair. I put in a medium amount of effort and emerged with a deserved B. The exam was very straightforward and exactly what you would expect had you paid attention in lectures.

I have had him twice: English Lit and Medieval Lit, both of which I did all the reading, went to every class and got a low mark.  Great prof, expects a lot, and yes I thought I did amazing on the exam and must of done horrible.  Yet, a friend of mind passed who attended less then half the classes.  Great prof but for that reason I hate his guts.

This prof has a lot to offer a student interested in Mediaeval literature.  I was very interested, but found it waned as the course continued.  The work load was pretty unreasonable compared to my other 3rd year profs who realized theirs was not the only class I was taking.  I am aware that I could not hack it, but I'm certainly not the only one.

Very clever man, very high demands. Speaking to him on office hours will help you loads. He challenges you, but it's worth it, and he cares so much about his subject matter that it makes it much more interesting to the student. Would definitely marry him.
ENG2130 was b.o.r.i.n.g. If you expected an interesting or easy class just run now. Rector is a nice guy but takes his subject a bit too seriously and marks exams hard.
HARD!!! ruined my transcript! nice guy though.

Hard marker. I had received A's on all my papers prior to taking his course, even from Jennifer Panek/April London!He's nice, not intimidating. His exam questions were really hard- the types of questions you either know or you don't. This was probably the hardest teacher I've ever had throughout the whole of my English Degree. Such a demanding clas

Great guy, totally knows his stuff. Enthusiastic teacher, which is a real feat for Medieval Lit (SNORE)! I finally discovered by the third essay that you HAVE to write exactly what he wants to hear, otherwise you're toast. Independent thinking will get you nowhere, so just form a thesis based on exactly what's in your lecture notes.

His assignments were so rigid and boring.  He is somewhat of an interesting lecturer but I would not recommend him as a first choice at all.  I found myself really dreading his class because of his "think inside the box" attitude.  Good for people who want to rewrite info without adding creativity, otherwise...just say no
ENG1122 was admittedly not my favourite course, but he made it pretty fun. His marking was easy and his lectures were good. Passionate. Intelligent. Nice guy. Recommended.
good guy, down to earth.
So amazing - enthusiastic, approachable, insightful, articulate. And distractingly goodlooking - or am I the only one who finds eloquence and intelligence really hot?

You need to write notes fast to remember everything, then regurgitate it all in a short time frame for exams.  This class was hard for me because I couldn't remember or write fast enough on tests. Basically tell him exactly what he wants to here.  I felt he favoured English students who participated in discussion. Good sense of humour though.

Awesome Prof!! He manages to relate his teachings to things us yougens actually understand. He makes it as fun as possible and actually considers our views. Average workload i guess. The only I found troubling were his expectations. I just didn't get exactly what he was looking for. But I still did ok. Definitely take a class with him if you can! :
LOVE him!! Sometimes his writing on the board tends to be a little all over the place, but he'll clarify in a heartbeat! Cute, fun, engaging, and helpful!
I don`t know who rated this man as hot...but you need glasses as thick as his if you think that.
Very good prof. Makes Medieval Lit. pleasurable (which is not easy). What I thought would be my worst class quickly became my favourite. It's definitely worth taking a class with him if you can!
Professor Rector is the best EVER! He's cute, and his discussions and lectures are super easy and fun to follow! I'm always captivated!
i love this man. he's so hot it's almost distracting.
I have nothing but good things to say about him. He takes boring subjects and makes them interesting. He's down-to-earth, easy to understand and helpful. On top of it all, he's very cute.

Good prof.  Subject matter was fascinating.  The only beef I have with him is that he tends to treats students as if they're babies who don't read books (which may or may not be true).  Amusing sense of humour.

Articulate, witty, knowledgeable, warm, funny, helpful, and adorable. I absolutely don't understand the negative reveiws about him, because he's even kind and helpful to stupid people. Unbelievable professor - take him any chance you get.
He's extremely dogmatic and set in his ways.  If you agree with him, that's good, but if you don't....   I suggest you avoid him on the chance that you don't.

He is smart, funny, helpful, and CUTE! Great lectures. Reciting the 18 GP lines isn't so bad; he's very encouraging. His workshop on essay writing was amazing, and totally voluntary on his part. He wants you to improve and become a better writer. I was actually sad when this class was over. I loved every minute. Now I'm a big fan of both Geoffreys!

Fantastic prof, with an encyclopaedic knowledge and an extraordinarily subtle and sophisticated way of thinking.  He's a joy to listen to, extremely enlightening, and a nice, friendly man to boot.  Anyone pursuing English as a career would want to be like him so soon out of PhD.
Totally lame. Decided to go all the way to Carleton just to avoid taking his dumb class. He is both insulting and pretetious as well as being disorganized.
Jerk...that is all I have to say...

Please grow up. I have never seen a man have so many hissy fits. If you want a class to respect you this is not the way to do it. And when you ask a class to write an extremely short essay, please don't then turn around and deduct marks for arguments not being "flushed out."

Really fun class! King Arthur isn't for everybody, but he made it really accessible. Cute, funny and really easy going. Good classroom atmosphere, which is always fun. Course load a little heavy, but go to class and you should be fine - and going to class is never a chore. Totally recommend! :)
He is an extremely nice guy and I enjoyed his class...I would take him again in the future...
I was dreading taking Chaucer, but Professor Rector made me really enjoy going to that class.  He is very clear, helpful, and a fair marker.  Take a class with him if you can!

I've never had a prof that made me want to go to class as much as Professor Rector did. He was extremely helpful and my writing has improved immensely in one semester because of him. My advice is to take a class with him. He was really great!!

Shows his human side: witty, comfortable, interesting, very approachable-he's not just a talking head at the front of the class. He's very helpful in structuring essays, and his marking is fair (expects students to do thier best-good bull**** metre). Plus...Hello Handsome!

He is funny, clear, extremely intelligent, and very willing to help. He also knows his stuff really well,is kind, and is a snappy dresser :) Take him if you can, for he has helped my writing immeasurably and makes me actually look forward to coming to class.
Great professor! So brilliant it is almost scary. He expects a lot from his students but he also gives a lot of himself. Very fair and a great lecturer.
